Final Answer:

Here are three highly-rated science fiction movies that meet the criteria:

1. Inception (2010)
   - Director: Christopher Nolan
   - Release Date: July 16, 2010
   - Main Plot Points: 
     - Dom Cobb is a skilled thief who specializes in extracting information from people's minds while they dream.
     - He's offered a chance to regain his old life by performing "inception" - planting an idea into a target's subconscious.
     - Cobb and his team must navigate multiple layers of dreams to complete their mission.
   - IMDB Rating: 8.8/10
   - Positive Review: [User review praising the film's originality and complexity](https://www.imdb.com/review/rw2265283/)
   - Negative Review: [User review criticizing the plot holes and lack of emotional depth](https://www.imdb.com/review/rw2270600/)

2. Blade Runner 2049 (2017)
   - Director: Denis Villeneuve
   - Release Date: October 6, 2017
   - Main Plot Points:
     - K, a new blade runner, uncovers a secret that could destabilize society.
     - His discovery leads him on a quest to find Rick Deckard, a former blade runner missing for 30 years.
     - The plot involves the possibility of replicants reproducing biologically.
   - Metacritic Score: 81/100
   - Positive Review: [Critic review praising the film's visuals and themes](https://www.imdb.com/review/rw3824802/)
   - Negative Review: [User review criticizing the pacing and plot](https://www.imdb.com/review/rw3831282/)

3. Alien (1979)
   - Director: Ridley Scott
   - Release Date: June 22, 1979
   - Main Plot Points:
     - The crew of the space freighter Nostromo investigates a distress signal from an alien vessel.
     - They encounter a deadly extraterrestrial creature that begins hunting them.
     - The survivors must find a way to destroy the alien and escape.
   - IMDB Rating: 8.5/10
   - Positive Review: [User review praising the film's atmosphere and tension](https://www.imdb.com/review/rw0052776/)
   - Negative Review: [User review criticizing the pacing and character development](https://www.imdb.com/review/rw1690360/)

